@20433 = ~Bellowing War Axe +3~
@20434 = ~Kurg the Bellower, a dwarf whom lived Dorn's Deep during the golden era during the alliance with the elves of the Seldarine, was enamoured with both song and music that were part of the elves's culture.  He wanted to share his enthusiam with his fellow dwarves, and set about learning to sing and play from elf musicians.  The elves were a bit apprehensive at first, as they'd never heard of a dwarven bard, but nevertheless they took him under their tutelage.  Unfortunately, despite his best efforts, whenever he would perform what he had learned, the dwarves of the deep would only laugh and likened his song to that of a bleating goat.  Others would disparage his efforts by shouting: "Ye cannae even carry an axe, much less a tune!"

Undeterred, Kurg sought help from one of his elven tutors, and the two set about forging an enchanted hand axe that would reverberate with Kurg's voice when he sang into it, resulting in the most unique and melodic tone.  At his next performance, the dwarves were both shocked and utterly delighted, marvelling at how such a wondeful sound could be produced with an axe as an instrument.  During the last days of the Deep, as the dwarves struggled against the invading orcish hordes, Kurg's song enfused them with courage and strength, allowing them to fight longer and harder than they would have been otherwise.

To this day, Kurg's disembodied voice can sometimes still be heard in the halls, bellowing a doleful dirge.

